Thema unter Rückgriff auf eine Vielfalt literarischer Gattungen.Der Band ist Hanns Christof Brennecke zum 70. Geburtstag gewidmet.  aThe Imperium Romanum was marked by a diverse and differentiated history of reciprocal interaction with the church and theology. The study examines this ever-changing relationship, encompassing a broad time span from the first to the sixth century. The essays include both the Eastern and Western parts of the Imperium and its successor states, and explore the theme by drawing from a wide range of literary genres.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAntike. 4aKirchengeschichte. 4aNeues Testament. 4aTheologie. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aNew Testament.  aantiquity.  achurch history.  atheology.1 aAllen, Pauline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergjan, Silke-Petra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrecoll, Volker Henning, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraumann, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeil, Uta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeil, Uta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLindemann, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLöhr, Winrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarkschies, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeier, Mischa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMühlenberg, Ekkehard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProstmeier, Ferdinand R., 